<h2>%%ReferenceStyle%%Lecture or lecture notes online</h2>
<hr>
Avoid where possible!
<br><br>
It is better to do the research and refer back to the original source yourself. Ask the lecturer for a reference list for their lecture if necessary. If the lecture material is available in electronic format, for example, on vUWS, follow the format for the citation of electronic sources. 
<br><br>
<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br><br>
Omit http:// or https:// from the URL. A description of the source can also be added if clarity is needed, at the end of the Works Cited entry.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author&#8217;s name. &#34;Title of Lecture.&#34; Unit name, Day Month. and Year, Venue of lecture, URL. Description.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br><br>
Abbreviate the word <em>University</em> to <em>U</em>. For further information on common academic abbreviations, see 1.6.2 in the <a href="http://west-sydney-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/UWS-ALMA:default_scope:UWS-ALMA21186157620001571" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MLA Handbook (8th edition)</a>. 
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s name">Smith, A</span>.
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Lecture">Pacific Island Quilting</span>.&#34; 
	<span class="hover" title="Unit name">Women 110</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Day Month and Year">28 Mar. 2056</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Venue of Lecture">U of Auckland</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="URL">learning.griffith.edu.au/@@11F0F4DC6CD3AFBB8C1CDC875741FF3D/courses/1/1004CCJ_3075_MG/content/_3329051intelligence%20</span>.
	<span class="hover" title="Description">Lecture</span>.
</blockquote>
