<hr>
<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
When you use another person&#8217;s ideas or words in your writing, include the author&#8217;s name, in parentheses, immediately following the cited material. 
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (Smith).
</blockquote>
<br>
Or include the author&#8217;s name in your sentence.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith suggested in a recent lecture that contemporary quilting has developed a hybrid form.
</blockquote>
